menu_status_stocks
[TITLE]The Manual: Stocks[/TITLE]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]How to Get Here[C:7:0:0]
[B]
If you have a bookkeeper, press [IKEY:D_STATUS] from the main view, scroll to "Stocks" and press [IKEY:SELECT].
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Description[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Here you can view every single object on the map.
Use [IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_UP][IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_DOWN][IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_LEFT][IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_RIGHT][IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_PAGEUP][IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_PAGEDOWN] to scroll.
[B]
There are two modes.  One compresses the item list for convenience, and one displays the items individually in a list.  When you are in
the individual list, you can view an object's description or zoom to its location on the map.
[B]
Numbers in brown with question marks indicate that your bookkeeper has not yet put in enough office time for you to be able to expand the corresponding item type into a list of individual items.  Brown numbers are also rounded according to your bookkeeping precision level.
